									<p><span data-contrast="auto">In the past three years, our world has evolved tremendously with the shake of big data and machine intelligence, and the Hong Kong is also expanding its resources on server acquisition and AI research support</span><span data-contrast="auto">. </span><span data-contrast="auto">This has given HKU IDS many opportunities to revolutionize fundamental research, technology, and education in the dynamic field of data science. </span><span data-ccp-props="{}"> </span></p><p><span data-contrast="auto">As we enter 2025, the Institute remains dedicated to its mission of nurturing top-tier researchers and students in data science and machine intelligence. Since its establishment in 2022, the number of our research talents, including faculty members and postgraduate students, has grown rapidly from just a few individuals to over 60. This growth has provided a strong foundation for IDS to expand and develop. Faculty members recruited through the HKU-100 Global Professoriate Recruitment Campaign are co-hosted with various departments and Faculties at HKU.</span><span data-contrast="auto"> </span><span data-ccp-props="{}"> </span></p><p><span data-contrast="auto">We wish to make continuous endeavours in sharpening research and education in data science.</span> <span data-contrast="auto">Let me also take this chance to express our sincere gratitude to the University for supporting our team along the way.</span><span data-ccp-props="{}"> </span></p><p><span data-ccp-props="{}">HKU IDS shall continue to strive for excellence in our three strategic research areas, (1) Fundamental data science; (2) Explainable AI and Human-Machine Interplays; and (3) Smart society. These areas will serve as the pillars of our research and innovation efforts, addressing critical challenges and opportunities in the field of data science and machine intelligence. Furthermore, through collaborations with other units, industry partners, and governmental bodies, HKU IDS aims to raise public awareness of technologies associated with data science and machine intelligence, focusing on issues like data security, privacy, and fairness. We have launched a series of programmes in collaboration with internal bodies and industrial sectors, across audience from academia, enterprises, and of course undergraduate students. I am confident that through collective efforts, we can position the new HKU IDS as a leading data science hub globally, setting new benchmarks for academic excellence and societal impact. </span></p><p><span data-contrast="auto">Please visit our website to explore the opportunities and collaborations that we offer. I eagerly anticipate the opportunity to collaborate with you closely in the future!</span></p><p id="" style="text-align: right;"><strong>Professor Yi MA</strong><br id="" /><span class="TextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0" lang="EN-HK" xml:lang="EN-HK" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0">Director of the HKU IDS</span></span><span class="LineBreakBlob BlobObject DragDrop SCXW57860186 BCX0"><span class="SCXW57860186 BCX0"> </span><br class="SCXW57860186 BCX0" /></span><span class="TextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0" lang="EN-HK" xml:lang="EN-HK" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0">Professor</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0">, Chair of Artificial Intelligence </span></span><span class="LineBreakBlob BlobObject DragDrop SCXW57860186 BCX0"><span class="SCXW57860186 BCX0"> </span><br class="SCXW57860186 BCX0" /></span><span class="TextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0" lang="EN-HK" xml:lang="EN-HK" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW57860186 BCX0">June 30, 2025</span></span><span class="EOP SCXW57860186 BCX0" data-ccp-props="{}"> </span></p>								</div>
